          <from>MR. YOUNGER</from>
          <p>MR. YOUNGER : Mr. Speaker, after a couple of weeks of asking almost the same question, you'd think you'd get a better answer at this point, with some detail. It's almost like the government is incapable of multi-tasking. The thing is, the minister will talk about cleaner, cheaper energy from Muskrat Falls and, of course, he probably knows that it has been reported in Newfoundland and Labrador that the price of that energy will be 16.54 cents a kilowatt hour in Newfoundland. We can assume that it might be higher here. We also know that it is only 8 per cent to 10 per cent, at most, of energy needs in Nova Scotia, so it makes sense that we are going to need energy from other sources.</p>
