      <debateSection>
        <heading>HEALTH &amp; WELLNESS - HOME OXYGEN SERV.: VENDORS - TENDERING</heading>
        <speech by="#41fa6a70-397a-4597-900b-20b957bef948">
          <from>MR. LEO GLAVINE</from>
          <p>MR. LEO GLAVINE : Well, it's a new question, Mr. Speaker, but it's going to have the same theme, and accountability and transparency is what it's all about. It should be paramount in any government's agenda. In April of this year government changed the tender process for home oxygen services from a process where clients could choose a vendor, based on the company that provided the best service, to one where customer choice is restricted, vendor decisions were decided by government using an arbitrary scoring process.</p>
